instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The digital twin system follows a C4 container architectural model and is deployed in six Docker containers to separate concerns and simplify orchestration. The containers are: (1) an MQTT broker that serves as the central signaling medium for inter-service communication; (2) a twin core container housing the simulation engine and state model that represents the physical gantry crane; (3) a data store container (e.g., InfluxDB) that persists time‑series sensor and telemetry data; (4) a gateway service container responsible for ingesting sensor data from the physical crane’s onboard Raspberry‑Pi; (5) a web dashboard container that visualizes the twin’s state and analytics for operators; and (6) a monitoring/alerts container that performs anomaly detection and generates notifications. The containers communicate through MQTT topics and shared database access, creating a decoupled yet coordinated runtime environment that facilitates maintenance, scaling, and clear separation of duties within the twin system."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "A Continuous Validation Service continuously compares the measured execution of trajectories against the simulated trajectories produced by the dynamic model. Discrepancies beyond configured tolerances are flagged for further inspection, ensuring that the Digital Twin maintains fidelity to real‑world behaviour."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "All inter‑component communication occurs over a local area network. Core services (Control Application, Logging Application, Trajectory Generator Service, Simulation Service, Continuous Validation Service) exchange messages via a lightweight MQTT broker; each service subscribes to the appropriate topics and publishes its status or telemetry. The Physical Crane Interface communicates with the crane controller hardware via a native TCP socket. No explicit bandwidth or latency metrics are specified in the document, and the document does not describe redundancy or security mechanisms beyond the MQTT broker’s presence."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The digital twin components are intended for on‑premise deployment on the host machine that directly controls the gantry crane. The Python containers run as local processes, utilizing a single TimescaleDB instance for persistent time‑series data. No cloud or edge deployment options are described, and the deployment model is a monolithic, single‑host architecture with no explicit scaling provisions beyond the modular container design outlined in the container diagram."
]

